com.epam.training.command

Interface ICommand

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AddBuildCommand, AddFeatureCommand, AddMemberCommand, AddProjectCommand, AuthCommand, BackHomeCommand, ChangeLanguageCommand, CloseIssueCommand, DeleteIssueCommand, EditFeatureCommand, EditIssueCommand, EditMemberCommand, EditProjectCommand, EditUserPassCommand, IssueInfoCommand, ListFeaturesCommand, ListIssuesCommand, ListMembersCommand, ListProjectsCommand, LogoutCommand, NoCommand, ReopenIssueCommand, SubmitIssueCommand, UpdatePassCommand, UpdatePersonalDataCommand

    public interface ICommand
    Interface ICommand is an interface that will be implemented by all Command classes that process data received from JSPs. It contains just one method that will be invoked by a Servlet (Controller) in order to process the request and redirect it to a chosen JSP.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Vasili Andreev
